question.title: What will be the State Bank of Pakistan's target policy rate as of May 1, 2026?
question.description:
This question tracks the exact target policy rate set by the State Bank of Pakistan (SBP) as of May 1, 2026. The policy rate is a critical tool for managing inflation and economic growth in Pakistan, influencing commercial interest rates and the value of the Pakistani Rupee.

`{"format":"bot_tournament_question","info":{"hash_id":"47ebb9c64990e164"}}`
question.resolution_criteria: This question resolves to the value of the State Bank of Pakistan (SBP) target policy rate (also known as the 'Policy Rate') in effect at 11:59 PM UTC on May 1, 2026. The resolution will be based on the official 'Monetary Policy Statements' published by the State Bank of Pakistan on its official website (https://www.sbp.org.pk/) or [credible sources](https://www.metaculus.com/faq/#definitions).
question.fine_print: The target policy rate is the primary signaling rate set by the Monetary Policy Committee (MPC). If the SBP transitions to a different primary policy instrument or name for the target rate, the rate that serves the equivalent function of setting the overnight repo/reverse-repo corridor midpoint or target will be used. Data revisions published after May 1, 2026, will not be considered unless they correct a clerical error regarding the rate actually in effect on that date.
